description: This grand loop around Woy Woy follows the Woy Woy Foreshore and much of Brisbane Waters National Park, including Warrah Lookout.

markers.description: Get the train to Woy Woy using transportnsw.info.
From the station cross Brisbane Water Dr and follow the footpath left on the other side.
Follow The Boulevarde to the right.
Follow Brick Wharf Rd along the waterfront.
Follow the sign left to the Lions Park.
There is a toilet block at the Lions Park.
From the Lions Park follow the shared path along the waterfront.
Follow the end the path to the right out of the park.
Follow Blackwall Road to the left.
Cross at the pedestrian crossing and follow Memorial Ave around the right side of Blackwall Mountain.
There are amenities at the servo along Memorial Drive.
At the roundabout continue straight along Barrenjoey Rd.
At the next roundabout follow the sign to Ettalong to the left.
From the corner of Bourke Rd follow Memorial Ave to the right.
At the intersection continue straight on Memorial Ave past the RSL.
Cross The Esplanade and continue to the waterfront.
There are amenities at The Box Park.
From The Box Park follow The Esplanade to the right.
Follow The Esplanade to Umina Beach.
From the corner of The Esplanade follow the footpath to surf club to the left.
From the surf club follow the beach access. There are amenities at the surf club.
From the surf club follow Umina Beach to the right.
At the end of the beach follow the access trail to the carpark.
From the carpark follow Mount Ettalong Rd to the left. There is a toilet block at the carpark.
Carefully follow the shoulder of Mount Ettalong Rd a short distance to the trailhead on the left.
From the trailhead follow the path around Umina Point.
From the end of the path follow the access trail to Pearl Beach to the left.
Follow Pearl Beach to the headland on the other side.
There is a toilet block at the picnic area.
From the picnic area follow Pearl Parade to the left. There are amenities at the corner.
From the corner of Pearl Parade follow Tourmaline Ave to the right.
At the intersection follow Diamond Rd to the left across the bridge.
After the bridge follow Crystal Ave to the right to the Pearl Beach Arboretum.
But why though?
markers.title: Wild Piano
markers.instruction: Visit this location to earn the mystery trophy

markers.description: At the arboretum enter the gated trailhead on the left.
From the trailhead follow the Pearl Beach Patonga Firetrail up the ridge.
Access the fenced lookout from the left side of the trail.
+10mOptionally there is a second unfenced lookout a short distance further along the track.
Let the tourists enjoy the fenced lookout. Welcome to the club of locals who know better.
markers.title: I Can See My House from Here
markers.instruction: Visit this location to earn the mystery trophy

markers.description: Follow Doyles Track opposite the lookout to Warrah Car Park.
From the Warrah Car Park follow Warrah Trig Rd.
At the intersection follow the trail to the right along Patonga Dr.
Cross Patonga Dr to the gated trailhead on the left.
At the intersection follow the Great North Walk marker to the right.
At the intersection follow the Great North Walk marker to the right.
At the intersection follow the Great North Walk marker to the left.
At the intersection follow the park sign to Girakool.
Follow the Great North Walk martkers along Van Dahl's Firetrail.
Before the landfill, follow the Great North Walk sign left along the Hawkesbury Track
Cross the creek and follow the Hawkesbury Track up the ridge on the other side.
Follow the Hawkesbury Track around the fenceline of the landfill.
With luck the wind is blowing away from it.
markers.title: The View is Garbage
markers.instruction: Visit this location to earn the mystery trophy

markers.description: Follow the Great North Walk markers across the rocky sections.
At the end of the Hawkesbury Track follow Dillons Firetrail to the the right.
Follow Dillons Firetrail to the landfill.
Follow Dillons Firetrail to fenceline of the landfill.
Use the pedestrian gate at the end of the trail for access to the landfill access road.
Follow Nagari Rd away from the landfill.
If the entrance gates are closed, use the pedestrian gate on the right.
Follow Nagari Rd to the underpass under the railway.
Use the pedestrian tunnel on the right side of the underpass.
From the underpass cross Woy Woy Rd to Correa Bay Boat Ramp.
There is a toilet block at the picnic area.
From the boat ramp follow the footpath along Woy Woy Rd.
At the intersection with Rawson Rd, follow Woy Woy Rd to the right.
Before the railway crossing, use the pedestrian tunnel on the left side of Woy woy Rd.
There is a toilet block near the bus stop.
From the other side of the pedestrian tunnel follow Railway St to the left.
Follow the footpath along the station carpark.
From the roundabout follow the footpath straight to the station.
Plan your return trip from Woy Woy at transportnsw.info.
